Package org.kortforsyningen.proj

Class Units

Object
Units
public final class Units
extends Object
A set of predefined units of measurements used by PROJ. Units of measurement are represented by the standard Unit interface, which is implemented by external libraries. PROJ-JNI uses whatever JSR-363 implementation is found on the classpath at the time this Units class is initialized. If such implementation is found, then the constants in this class (DEGREE, METRE, SECOND, etc.) are references to Unit instances provided by that implementation. Otherwise those constants are references to an internal fallback implementation with limited capability.

Providing a JSR-363 implementation is optional but recommended if operations such as unit arithmetic (e.g. METRE.divide(SECOND)) and unit conversions (e.g. GRAD.getConverterTo(DEGREE)) are to be performed.

Since:
1.0
